==English==

===Etymology===
1792, from {{etyl|fr|en}} {{term|acclimater|lang=fr}}, from {{term|à|lang=fr}} + {{term|climat||climate|lang=fr}}  from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|ad|lang=la}} + {{term|climat|lang=la}}, (English {{term|climate|lang=en}}) from {{etyl|grc|en}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} – see {{term|climate|lang=en}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ə.ˈklaɪ.mət/|lang=en}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˈæk.lɪ.meɪt/|lang=en}}
* {{audio|en-us-acclimate.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|acclimat}}

# {{context|transitive|chiefly|US|lang=en}} To [[habituate]] to a [[climate]] not native; to [[acclimatize]].
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To [[adjust]] to a new [[environment]]; not necessarily a wild, natural, earthy one.
# {{context|intransitive|lang=en}} To become accustomed to a new climate or environment.

